exports[`emitProcessPack > every emitted text file matches its snapshot > gates/spec-approval-gate.md 1`] = `
"# spec-approval-gate — gate spec stub

> **Not live gate code.** This file is a deterministic spec stub emitted by
> the process-pack emitter. Live hook/gate scripts (concrete event binding,
> matcher authoring, false-fire evaluation, lazy-agent judging) are a later
> factory task; until then this document is the gate's contract.

- Kind: gate
- Disposition: generate — generated by the process factory as part of this pack
- Governance phase at birth: shadow

## Intent (L2 rationale)

The constraint is policy-shaped: only a blocking gate turns approval-before-emit from a remembered rule into an enforced one.

## Event

Unbound in this stub. The concrete Claude Code hook event is selected when
the live gate script is authored; the firing point it must implement is
described by the matcher intent below.

## Matcher intent

Block progress exactly while any condition guarded by the traced truths
below is unsatisfied — and never otherwise (false-fire evaluation gates the live version).

## Enforcement

- Phase "shadow": observe and record violations; never block.
- Decision rule: If any CTQ records a defect in a scan window, file an improvement proposal in the needs-review queue; two consecutive defective windows escalate to the operator.
- Control plan: every factory scan run, at least once per week — file an improvement proposal for operator review; never auto-apply.
- Lazy-agent test: before this gate leaves shadow, a judge must answer
  "what is the cheapest path past this gate?" with evidence; cosmetic-
  compliance answers fail the gate (design §6).

## Provenance — traced truths (verbatim)

- **t1** [constraint]: "A process spec must be operator-approved before emission."
  - Rationale: HITL stop-gate at the end of the spec stage; a factory that emits unapproved specs removes the human from the only structural checkpoint.

Traced constraints (Theory of Constraints analysis):

- **c1** [policy]: "Nothing enforces spec-approval-before-emit today: emission is reachable without an operator-approved spec."

## Relationships

- depends_on: factory-intake
- complements: (none)
- composes_with: (none)
- supersedes: (none)
- binds_tools: (none)
"
`;

exports[`emitProcessPack > every emitted text file matches its snapshot > hooks/deploy-discipline-hook.md 1`] = `
"# deploy-discipline-hook — hook spec stub

> **Not live hook code.** This file is a deterministic spec stub emitted by
> the process-pack emitter. Live hook/gate scripts (concrete event binding,
> matcher authoring, false-fire evaluation, lazy-agent judging) are a later
> factory task; until then this document is the hook's contract.

- Kind: hook
- Disposition: generate — generated by the process factory as part of this pack
- Governance phase at birth: shadow

## Intent (L2 rationale)

Deploy discipline must fire on the deploy action itself: a hook on the deploy path checks draft-PR-only and metrics-manifest presence at the moment they can still be enforced.

## Event

Unbound in this stub. The concrete Claude Code hook event is selected when
the live hook script is authored; the firing point it must implement is
described by the matcher intent below.

## Matcher intent

Fire exactly when a condition guarded by the traced truths below is at
risk — and never otherwise (false-fire evaluation gates the live version).

## Enforcement

- Phase "shadow": observe and record violations; never block.
- Decision rule: If any CTQ records a defect in a scan window, file an improvement proposal in the needs-review queue; two consecutive defective windows escalate to the operator.
- Control plan: every factory scan run, at least once per week — file an improvement proposal for operator review; never auto-apply.

## Provenance — traced truths (verbatim)

- **t2** [constraint]: "Every emitted pack must carry its metrics manifest (CTQs, baseline, decision rule, governance phase)."
  - Rationale: Sensing is distributed: a pack born without its manifest can never report outcomes, so it can never be improved honestly.
- **t3** [constraint]: "Deploys land only as draft PRs into engram-plugins, never as direct pushes."
  - Rationale: D-016/D-065: every deployment gets adversarial review; the factory holds no merge authority.

## Relationships

- depends_on: spec-approval-gate
- complements: (none)
- composes_with: (none)
- supersedes: (none)
- binds_tools: (none)
"
`;

